  "response": "While fertile cervical mucus makes pregnancy more likely, it is still possible to get pregnant without it. Cervical mucus helps sperm travel and survive, but some sperm can still reach the egg in its absence. However, reduced or absent cervical mucus can make conception more challenging. Factors like hormonal issues, certain medications, or medical conditions can affect cervical mucus production. If you're experiencing difficulties conceiving, consulting a healthcare professional is recommended.",
